column1: 148004;instagram;2018-12-07 20:08:48;FALSE;story time! back in may of this year
column2: i did something i’ve wanted to do for 7 years. i got my first tattoo by the talented @joemiller.art! this holds a lot of meaning for me - a lot of which has to do with letting go of control. the 3 maple leaves represent my 2 sisters and i growing up in ma with the most beautiful foliage that i miss every year! my favorite colors are red
column3: orange and yellow because of the leaves that would line our streets and fill our yard every fall. the watercolor style was really important to me because not only do i find it really beautiful
column4: but i am weirdly intimidated by watercolor as an art form. i’ve never felt like i had any control with it’s flowy nature
column5: and my anxiety has always demanded that i could control the paint i use
column6: hence my use of acrylic and oil before starting with makeup and body paint. (ugh anxiety!) joe’s way of working meant that i would send him a couple of inspo photos and (the hardest part for me) i wouldnt see a sketch until the day of the tattoo. i was committed to letting go of control and trusting another artist throughout this entire process...and that meant that i didn’t even see the entire tattoo’s full form until it was on my body. i’m not going to lie - i was really nervous. what if it didn’t look like i wanted it to look? what if i hated it and it was on my body forever? what if?! i decided to acknowledge my fears
column7: let them exist and work through them anyway. i knew this whole exercise was important for me to heal in several ways. the tattoo took 7.5 hours and it was on my ribs! ouch. i did a lot of yoga breathing throughout the process and i was fine 😂. the most important part of me getting this tattoo the way i did was that it actually helped me work through a trauma i had experienced 5 years ago this christmas. i was raped. once this tattoo was on my body
column8: i got to reclaim my body as my own again. no one had ever assaulted this version of my body. no one had decided they had the right to do something to it that they had no business doing. it was mine...and so i kept it off social media for a while even though i am so proud of how beautiful it is. i feel like i can share now. 💕;;en;;@joemiller.art!;;;;0;;juliehasit;Julie Hassett;;0;False;32;0;0;207;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/e682f5d4f00e9b596a1cecca3c7b0508/5D1C83E8/t51.2885-15/e35/46067495_1810959452363531_3331657463319733950_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;story time! back in may of this year

no.  my biggest failure was in not starting sooner.

column2: i said million-club and i’m talking about dollars..) but i digress
column3: i did not start back then and i am not a million club member. yet. i started coaching at the end of july 2018.

column4: how to get started or where to go from where they were. i’ve fostered friendships of the nature that i didn’t know existed with women who were barely making it
column5: and are now crushing it. together
column6: we are conquering our worlds. together

column1: 에바 그린이 출연했던 2004년 작 '몽상가들'은 베르나르도 베르톨루치가 과연 거장인가 라는 의구심을 갖게 할 정도의 졸작에 가까웠다. 격렬한 사상가이며 그 자신 열렬한 영화광이기도 했던 젊은 시절을 그린 자전적 영화일 것이라는 기대와 달리 정작 이 영화는 젊은이들의 '섹스 잔치'로 끝나 버렸다. 젊은이들에게 잃어버린 이상을 찾기 위해 만든 영화라는 그의 캐치프레이즈가 무색하기만 했다.
이후 10년만에 14살 소년의 성장기를 그린 '미 앤 유'를 선보여 호평을 받았다. 하지만 얼마후 그는 암과의 투병생활로 인해 작품활동을 중단해야 했다.
베르톨루치는 언젠가 ""극장은 여전히 우리 모두가 함께 꿈을 꾸고 펼칠 수 있는 성당과도 같은 곳""이라고 말한 적이 있다. 영화에 대한 그의 짙은 애정이 살아 숨쉬고 있음을 느낄 수 있다.
독보적이고 혁명적이었던 명장 베르톨루치는 이제 가고 없다. 그가 영화사에 남긴 논란은 다가오는 새로운 시대에도 계속 될 것이다. 그리고 그의 주옥 같은 작품들은 또한 영원히 우리의 가슴 속에 남아 있을 것이다.

column2: 몽상가들 ) ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 에바 그린이 출연했던 2004년 작 '몽상가들'은 베르나르도 베르톨루치가 과연 거장인가 라는 의구심을 갖게 할 정도의 졸작에 가까웠다 . 격렬한 사상가이며 그 자신 열렬한 영화광이기도 했던 젊은 시절을 그린 자전적 영화일 것이라는 기대와 달리 정작 이 영화는 젊은이들의 '섹스 잔치'로 끝나 버렸다 . 젊은이들에게 잃어버린 이상을 찾기 위해 만든 영화라는 그의 캐치프레이즈가 무색하기만 했다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 이후 10년만에 14살 소년의 성장기를 그린 '미 앤 유'를 선보여 호평을 받았다 . 하지만 얼마후 그는 암과의 투병생활로 인해 작품활동을 중단해야 했다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 베르톨루치는 언젠가 `` 극장은 여전히 우리 모두가 함께 꿈을 꾸고 펼칠 수 있는 성당과도 같은 곳 '' 이라고 말한 적이 있다 . 영화에 대한 그의 짙은 애정이 살아 숨쉬고 있음을 느낄 수 있다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 독보적이고 혁명적이었던 명장 베르톨루치는 이제 가고 없다 . 그가 영화사에 남긴 논란은 다가오는 새로운 시대에도 계속 될 것이다 . 그리고 그의 주옥 같은 작품들은 또한 영원히 우리의 가슴 속에 남아 있을 것이다 . ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ;"[('dreamers'

column2: nationwide teenage sensitization is unstoppable until we support children to grow in a society free of abuse

column1: when we give children opportunity to express themselves we will be amazed at the magnitude of what they are keeping to themselves.

lot of questions were raised during the sensitization_and_creating_a_safer_world_for_the_children with use of my body is my body programme - keeping children safe which range from: ° body safety ° assertive skills
° rape ° cultism ° renunciation of various forms of: • abuse • sexual harassment.
all these were addressed with simple illustration by our team from whrf
column2: gender development initiative (gendi) and child protection network

column1: story telling and drama is part of our strategy for our nationwide teenage sensitization project to enable the students to identify how special their bodies areas are. along with concept that nobody has the right to touch them in any way without their permission nor hurt them in any way.
we teach this concept  by using guidance and support from mybodyismybody
we hope by sharing our experiences others will see benefits of implementing such a program in their communities.
may we all continue to learn how to bring a better future for the children of our world.

column1: 148094;instagram;2018-12-07 21:35:57;FALSE;"16 ways to end violence towards girls
drawing on over 80 years of experience with some of the world's most at-risk girls
column2: we've put together a list of some of the most effective ways to tackle violence towards girls and women.

column1: 1. raise awareness of the dangers of harmful traditions

nagah practised female genital mutilation (fgm) in egypt for 17 years until she learned first-hand the devastating impact it can have on girls’ lives. she is helping rural families to learn about the facts and change their attitudes to help the practice come to an end.
2. tackle violence against girls in school
it is estimated that 246 million girls and boys are harassed and abused on their way to

column3: a ninth-grade student gained confidence from counselling sessions after being bullied. “i now feel confident. i no longer have thoughts of giving up on school. i tell my friends if they ever face troubles
column4: they should speak to the school counsellor

column1: 3. challenge and speak out about violence in the home
charlienne is determined to challenge beliefs around violence having seen her mother abused by her father.

column4: grew up in a violent household. now she’s determined to challenge the deeply ingrained beliefs that lead to gender-based violence in her community. “if my husband was to beat me
column5: i would report him to the police. violence against women should not be tolerated.” 4. transform attitudes towards harmful practices at multiple levels

column2: medical professionals and ex-practitioners are all coming together to bring an end to fgm
column3: which in some regions sees as much as 93% of women cut. now
column4: girls in the community are becoming empowered to fight back against this damaging tradition. “if i have a daughter she will not be cut. i will not allow it”

column1: 148120;instagram;2018-12-07 22:15:01;TRUE;;"very interesting that 4 out of the top 5 most dangerous are majority muslim countries.🤔🤔🤔 #repost @geographics.sv
note: the poll surveyed 548 experts on six different indices - healthcare

#maps #culture thomson reuters foundation surveys 548 women-rights-experts around the world to make a list of the most dangerous countries for woman. this survey took place from march to may 2018. here it is the list of the 5 most dangerous countries
column2: with the problems that woman face everyday. india has been declared the most dangerous country in the world for women
column3: the saddest aspect of this is that india has the second largest population of women in the world.

column1: 148176;instagram;2018-12-07 23:29:20;FALSE;guys. this is so fucking important. tonight
column2: i took this selfie at work to send to my boyfriend specifically to joke about how much of child i look like today
column3: something we joke about often. no filter
column4: no anything. this is me. moments afterwards
column6: a patron at my bar asked me if i was “dressing up tomorrow?” when i asked him what i could possibly be dressing up for on december 8th of all days
column7: he proceeded to tell me it was santacon and decided that it would be appropriate to ask if i was going to be wearing my “sexy santa costume” so he could come in and see me. when i told him that i was not dressing up tomorrow or ever nor would i be working
column8: he told me he was going to “make sure he’d find out when i was.” this is what i was wearing. this is why #metoo exists. this is why we need feminism. anyone who thinks that any sort of movement calling out sexual harassment is hyperbolic
column9: this is our day to day. i am so exhausted guys. fuck this shit. none of my male coworkers would have to deal with this. and none of them had to deal with someone saying something like that to them tonight. this man doesn’t even know my name. all i am to him is some warped fucking fantasy. we need to change. we’re better than this. care for yourselves and those close to you and put that out there into the universe ten fold. because i guarantee you a female you love had to deal with the same shit probably today but it was so normal that she didn’t even feel like wasting her breath on it. #nomore #metoo #fuckthis #sofuckingtired #feminism #smashthefuckingpatriarchy;;en;#METOO

column1: 148187;instagram;2018-12-08 00:10:12;FALSE;"i spent the morning in court supporting my tantra sister palki. she was raped by tj bartel in a tantra session and she asked me to go with her to face him
this morning was intense. i haven’t seen tj in years. when i saw him
column2: he put his hands in namaste as if we were friends. yes i have known him 15 years
column3: but we are not friends. it was as if he forgot to see i was standing right next to palki
column5: and forgetting that the last time i saw him he told me that he allows his clients to touch his genitals and give him blowjobs…which is not part of tantric healing sessions.

column2: the energy of the unknown for palki
column3: and even for me. palki turned to me and asked me to share my experience of tj
column4: this…it was this that i was nervous about..i took a moment to think about it and said yes i would. as i felt it would be good for the court to know that he rubs his genitals on women in healing sessions…even if he does have his underwear on and lets them do sexual acts with him.
she felt she was here on a mission
column5: not only to speak her truth
column6: but to stand in her power and that was incredible to witness!

column1: the judge ended up taking her case last as she wanted no one else in the room. she wasn’t sure even if this should be seen in a small claims court. but she listened
column2: she took the information in. i listened to palki
column3: how she shared he side so clear
column4: with confidence and how that brought up a lot of emotion for her. the judge said she didn’t need to share some parts
column5: as she had read what happened in her notes to her.

column2: i really was blown away at the wisdom of this women
column3: she asked some powerful questions… “do you have training in working with women that have this kind of trauma and how they’d respond to this kind of work”? tj kept avoiding the answer…finally the 3rd time she asked
column4: she said “yes or no”. he responded no.

column1: #colette es un homenaje a una personalidad demasiado avanzada y controversial para su época. un personaje tan controvertido y a la vez tan olvidado en la actualidad
column2: que estuvo demasiado fuera de las normas como para poderse enmarcar en cánones
column3: no simplemente narrativos dentro de un film
column4: sino para comprenderlos con la correcta dimensionalidad en su propio espacio/tiempo o trasladándolos a nuestros días
column5: donde el empoderamiento femenino y la identidad de género siguen luchando con vehemencia.

column1: excelente la música del compositor de ópera británico thomas adès
column2: que resulta un activo principal del film
column3: uno de los valores principales de la película; la partitura fue escrita expresamente para la pantalla por adès
column4: con su ágil piano y el trabajo de cuerdas que lo acompaña. muy buena la fotografía de giles nuttgens. unido a ello una exquisita puesta en escena
column5: vestuario incluido. keira knightley hace un espléndido papel
column6: liberándose del lastre que supone su marido
column7: reconociéndose como escritora e incluso permitiéndose el lujo de salir del armario. dominic west interpreta al arrogante y egoísta esposo también hace un papel bastante jugoso.

column1: la conjunción de west y knightley en pantalla inunda de seducción y perversidad esta relación a todas luces suigeneris y como una relación tan enervante de amor/odio
column2: sujeción/dominación y dependencia que no puede sino provocar interés morboso e intriga a partes iguales.

column1: aunque la película no profundiza en la literatura de colette
column2: sí lo hace en la época que le tocó vivir y sus circunstancias muchas veces adversas. pero sobre todo se centra en la figura de una mujer que representó un mensaje nuevo de manumisión y liberación. un biopic más centrado en el perfil personal e ideológico de la protagonista que en su vertiente artística. la perspectiva que ofrece
column3: no escapa al buen espectador que con el ingenio de la protagonista y su modernidad de amplio espectro
column5: las costumbres sexuales y el papel de la mujer en forma avanzada y rompedora para principios del pasado siglo.

column1: 148256;instagram;2018-12-08 02:32:40;FALSE;"नजरिया👇👇👇 *करीब के गाँव में दो सहेलियाँ 12 वीं की परीक्षा देने जा रही हैं और चलते हुए आपस में बातें कर रही हैं।*👇 सीता---: गीता
column2: तू तो बिल्कुल भी पढ़ाई नहीं करती है। गीता -- छोड़ न यार! पास हुए तो फिर 13
column4: 15 वीं की परीक्षा दो और फिर नौकरी वाला पति....😳 सीता-- : तो ? बढ़िया तो है। गीता--: क्या बढ़िया है ?  12 घंटों की नौकरी और तनख्वाह 25-30 हजार। फिर मुंबई-पूना जैसे बड़े शहरों में रहने जाओ। वहाँ किराए का घर होगा जिसमें आधी तनख्वाह चली जाएगी। फिर अपना खुदका घर चाहिए तो लोन लेकर 4-5 मंजिल ऊपर घर लो और एक गुफा जैसे बंद घर में रहो। लोन चुकाने में 15-20 साल लगेंगे और बड़ी किल्लत में गृहस्थी चलेगी। न त्यौहारों में छुट्टी न गर्मी में। सदा बीमारी का घर। स्वस्थ रहना हो तो ऑर्गेनिक के नाम पर 3-4 गुना कीमत देकर सामान खरीदो। और फाइनली वो नौकरी करने वाला नौकर ही तो होगा। तू सारा जोड़ घटाना गुणा भाग करले
column5: तेरी समझ में आ जाएगा। घर का खर्च नहीं चल पाया तो तुझे भी नौकरी करणी पडेगी...😫 और अगर परीक्षा में फेल हो गई तो किसी खेती किसानी वाले किसान से ब्याह दी जाउँगी। जीवन थोड़ा तकलीफदेह तो होगा लेकिन वो खुद का सच्चा मालिक होगा और मैं होऊँगी मालकिन। पैसे कम ज्यादा होंगे लेकिन सारे अपने होंगे
column6: कोई टेक्स का लफड़ा नहीं। सारा कुछ ऑर्गेनिक उपजाएँगे और वही खाएँगे। बीमारी की चिंता फिक्र ही नहीं
column8: पति 24 घंटे अपने साथ ही रहेगा। बाद में #metoo #metoo कर पछताणे का भी कोई चांस नहीं। सीता--- : मैं भी फेल ही हो जाती हूँ रे.....!!

column4: it gives me confidence and i feel pretty
column5: it makes me feel fucking good. i like to think of it as feeding the little girl within who use to love to play dress up. the thing is though most of the time
column6: it doesn't matter if we are wearing jeans and a t-shirt or a dress with heels. if we are going to get looks or comments it will happen regardless of what we are wearing. .

column1: i will never forget this time at my first job. i use to work at hallmark in the mall and i was sexually harassed by an older co-worker and when i told my boss about it she responded
column2: ""well look at you maddie. you're just going to have to get use to that kind of attention looking like that."" mind you i wasn't dressed up in anything special. i was wearing my work uniform
column3: black dress pants and some solid colored shirt. he didn't get in trouble or talked to. it was just shrugged off because
column4: i should be use to it? i was only about 16/17. that manager was so cruel towards me; some said it was because she was jealous but looking back
column5: maybe she was still hurting from a past experience she dealt with and didn't know how else to respond. (i quit shortly after.) .

column2: embrace that vibe from them and tell them they are beautiful. i try and compliment someone every day! just yesterday i was grocery shopping and an old woman was wearing a cat sweater and
column3: i'm a crazy cat lady so i told her i loved it! be the reason someone smiles today. .

column1: more women need to speak up. more men have to step up and own up to what they did and that it was wrong.

148486;instagram;2018-12-08 11:58:20;FALSE;- القبول المجتمعي لجريمة #التحرش_الجنسى يجعلها مستمرة. - مواجهة مرتكبي جرائم التحرش احد اهم عوامل تحطيم هواجس المتحرشين وافكارهم المغلوطه عن سعادة المرأة بالتحرش بها. - التمسك بالقانون والاصرار علي ملاحقة المتحرشين قضائيا سوف يساهم في تقليص جرائم العنف الجنسي.

- اقرت تعديلات قانونية في منتصف عام 2014 جعلت عقوبة التحرش تبداء من السجن 6 اشهر وحتي 5 سنوات ، وغرامات ماليه تبداء من 3 ألاف وحتي 50 ألف جنيه مصري، وتتضاعف العقوبة إذا تكرر الفعل من الجاني او إذا كان ذو سلطة او وصايه او ولايه قانونية علي المجني عليها  #قتلهم_التحرش

column1: 148492;instagram;2018-12-08 12:03:22;FALSE;"i really appreciate how she made me love myself a little more by each passing day. i used to make fun of myself. i used to ridicule and underestimate myself just because people don't find me beautiful. and that day
column2: she came. she never asked me to look beautiful. i don't remember if she ever did. nope
column3: never. i was amazed at the fact that still there are some people who love you inspite of your looks
column4: your body and your colour. there are people who make you comfortable in your own skin. i believe
column6: in search of pure soul rather than a perfect body. for some time
column7: i had forgotten that 'beauty lies in the eyes of beholder'. but
column8: she made me realize it. i found that person and i got the fact that 'the day you start loving yourself is the day you become some more beautiful.' all thanks to her - kimmi @peaceful_wild_

column3: and nervous darting eyes. people get quiet and don’t ask questions. this number is too big for us to be unable to speak freely about the atrocity of rape. i’m finding through these tough conversations that we as a culture don’t have the language to speak about these violations of our bodies- a fundamental element if we are to change things. we’re scared to discuss it
column7: it creates vulnerability in all parties of the conversation.

column1: we have to be willing to have uncomfortable conversations if things are going to change. i know miami isn’t usually the place to have this moments but without our presence in these spaces we will continue to only scratch the surface.
we must be willing to unearth these monstrous problems and deal with them directly instead of allowing them to stay buried
we must be brave. we must work to dismantle the patriarchal silence that blankets sexual violence against all people. silence is what holds us down. silence is the bedfellow of oppression. •

column1: 148643;instagram;2018-12-08 16:17:56;FALSE;one of my favorite things to explore with clients: why a behavior exists 💭. ——————————————— so often we jump straight to making shame-based meaning out of behavior (i.e. “i yelled at that person because i’ve always just been a jerk.”) when we explore behavior more deeply
column2: there is always a function. (this doesn’t excuse our behavior
column3: but if we want to behave differently it can be helpful to understand what maintains said behavior in the first place.) ——————————————— this is especially true with trauma. it can therefore be helpful to instead look at behavior as survival. how was my behavior really an attempt at self-preservation? column10: though: feelings will always be experienced

148663;instagram;2018-12-08 16:37:29;FALSE;“i hope women can be empowered by my story
column2: i'm not some total bad ass so i actually surprised myself when this happened. i think i just got angry enough to finally fight back after all the times of being yelled at and grabbed. this happened about 20 years ago.

column1: i was walking up to our local civic center one sunday morning to buy some tickets to a concert. the place was supposed to be open
column2: but it wasn't. and our smallish downtown is nearly deserted most sundays
column3: so it was just me on the street
column4: until i saw a guy walking up to me. the area in front of the civic center is literally all sidewalk
column5: so he could have easily kept his distance
column6: but he was coming right at me. my first thought was that i was going to be robbed since i had a purse full of cash for the tickets i was supposed to buy. but he walked right up to me and grabbed my boobs. just
column7: laid his hands right on them and gave a couple of squeezes. ""honk honk"" is what i thought
column8: as he did it. i also thought ""man
column9: that guy looks like meathead from all in the family."" about a second later
column11: my fight or flight finally kicked in
column12: and i screamed and punched the guy right in the face...”- anonymous. **full story in post. it gets so good.**

column2: send your stories to catscallingback@gmail.com or dm me. •

column1: #creative #girlssupportinggirls #girlpower #girlgang #streetharassment #harassmentstories #notyourbaby #timesup #metoo #femaleempowerment #womenempoweringwomen #womenempowerment #feminism #feminist #catscallingback";"“i hope women can be empowered by my story
column2: i am not some total bad ass so i actually surprised myself when this happened. i think i just got angry enough to finally fight back after all the times of being yelled at and grabbed. this happened about 20 years ago.

column1: i was walking up to our local civic center one sunday morning to buy some tickets to a conce. the place was supposed to be open
column2: but it wasn't. and our smallish downtown is nearly deseed most sundays
column3: so it was just me on the street
column4: until i saw a guy walking up to me. the area in front of the civic center is literally all sidewalk
column5: so he could have easily kept his distance
column6: but he was coming right at me. my first thought was that i was going to be robbed since i had a purse full of cash for the tickets i was supposed to buy. but he walked right up to me and grabbed my boobs. just
column7: laid his hands right on them and gave a couple of squeezes. ""honk honk"" is what i thought
column8: as he did it. i also thought ""man
column9: that guy looks like meathead from all in the family."" about a second later
column11: my fight or flight finally kicked in
column12: and i screamed and punched the guy right in the face...”- anonymous. **full story in post. it gets so good.**

column1: 148675;instagram;2018-12-08 17:06:51;FALSE;"i was watching a documentary on netflix about the “swipe” generation. the narrator talked about how skewed a vision of sex the younger generations have because they’ve been exposed to porn as their main staple of sex education. i never really thought about where i learned how to have sex. maybe it’s like one of those institutions such as child rearing that we just don’t get a book for until we’re a part of that sect. i’m hoping this project and so many other projects people have started
column2: bring awareness and therefore decrease the stigma and fear our society has around sex. porn cannot be blamed for violence. people have been violent towards each other way before the advent of porn. i guess i’m just hoping for and needing sexual violence to decrease around the world. how we are exposed to sex and sexuality leaves a lifelong impression. violence leads to violence. i’d love to break the cycle of violence now and heal the wounds of our world
column3: and make the future bright for all the young girls and boys who’ve not yet had sexual experiences. i wish everyone could have heart warming thoughts surrounding their first exposure to sex. it’s 2018 and we have long road ahead of us. let’s do this. (i think i sound like a pageant winner lol. but i really do want all those things.)

column1: په ټوله نړۍ کي په ټولنېزو رسنيو ښځېنه وې ځورول کيږي خو کچه يې دومره نده لکه په مونږ کي

زمونږ په ټولنه کي په يو اندازه لس سلنه ١٠% ښځېنه وې سواد لرونکې دې په دغو لسو کي دوه سلنه ښځېنه وې انټرنېټ کاروي او دغو دوه سلنو  ښځېنه وو کي يو سلنه ښځېنه وې انټرنېټ / فسبک/ انسټګرام او ټويټر د ټولنيز بدلون او سياسي ټولنيز فکر خورولو لپاره کاروي بيا مونږ نوي ٩٠%  نارينه چي هغو کي ښه لوستي روشنفکره سياسي ځوانان او لوی فيمنسټان دغو ښځېنه وو ته په ټولنيزو رسنيو لويې بلاوې جوړې شوې دې  له عادي بېسوادو خلګو يې د ځورونې بڼه ځکه جدا ده چي هغه مخامخ ځورونه کوي او روشنفکران يا فيمنسټان يې لږ بل شان  او خپلو کورونو کي خوېندو
column3: لوڼو ته د موبايل اجازه نه ورکوي خو د بل خوېندو ته په ډېره څالاکي په جدا بڼه مسجونو کوي

column1: ١ =د بېسوادانو ځورونه = ( سلام ته د کوم ځای يې/ عمر دي څو دی / ماسره ملګرتيا کوې کنه / ولي جواب نه راکوې ښايستې څه او څه

٢ = د سواد لرونکو ځورونې ( اغلې جوړ پخير / دغه ليکنه هتمن لوست کړه / که وخت ولرې د پلانکي ليکوال کتاب لوست کړه/ ولا دا د فسبک له خلګو نور انسان په تنګ شي / مونږ کومه خوا ته روان خلګ کومه خواته روان / اغلې يا خور که وخت ولرې بيا کله زنګ وکړه / ولا ته خو ډېره پوهه پښتنه يې ستا سوچ مي خوښ شو ځي او پسي ځي
چي روسته د هغې سوچ له ټولنيز فکر څخه و شخصي رومانتک ژوند ته راواړوي يا هغه له ټولنيز فکر او سوچ زړه ماتې کړي چي دلته يې زور تر ملي کاز او تاوان ووځي

که مو له دغه عمل څخه لاس وانخستل دغه پاته ګټه به هم دلاسه ورکړو ځکه دا وخت زمونږ په ټولنه کي ښځېنه وو ته د زړه ورکولو يا حوصلې ورکولو ډېره اړتيا ده ترڅو هغه خپل اولاد يا زمونږ را روان نسل مونږ ته وروزي

نوټ = د #metoo په نامه دغه اداره د نړۍ په ګڼشمېر هيوادونو کي د هغو خلګو په وړاندي کار کوي څوک چي په ښځېنه وو جنسي تېری، ټولنيزو رسنيو باندي جنسي ځورونې او نور ظلمونه کوي او دغه اداره بيخي په لنډ وخت کي ستاسو په غوښتنه مخالف لوری د قانون منګولو ته سپاري ښځېنه وې کولی شي دغه افليکېشن ډونلوډ کړي او د اړتيا په وخت يې وکاروي ځکه دغه انلاين اداره ده
بايد دغه تنظيم يا اداره په افغانستان کي ژر تر ژر پرانيستل شي ترڅو ښځېنه وې له جنسي تېري ، ځورونې او نورو ظلمونو وژغورل شي

column2: i would say we are confronting the backlash. i’m still too afraid to speak up in my language because i can expect to be criticised by japanese people. i’m seriously concerned about the unpopularity especially in japan because feminism is not attractive but intensive for not just boys but girls😬 so i want to try to make it more fashionable and friendly even for those don’t like politics. column1: a while ago my psychologist told me that i have ptsd. she was astounded no one had diagnosed it. i dove into research & it was like flicking through a transcript of my life.

i first recognised it reading michelle elman's book am i ugly? she describes obsessively checking locks in her home when feeling unsafe. i acquired that habit as a kid. i couldn’t sleep unless i’d checked every my room for the monster my parents couldn’t see. at 7
column2: i started self-harming. i developed insomnia at 8 & had brutal night terrors.

column1: in my teens i abused drugs & alcohol
column2: self-harmed religiously & was dangerously impulsive. i disassociated from the world.
i sought help & believed that i’d ‘cured’ my darkness. 2 years ago my symptoms resurged.

column1: i was elated & dejected when the #metoo movement took off. i was proud of those sharing their truth but i couldn’t put mine out there. it felt too taboo.
i won’t shame myself into silence anymore. so i guess this is the part where i tell you what this is really about…
i was groomed and sexually abused for 3 years as a child.

trauma overwhelmed my life for a long time but i no longer see it as some tragic story to be pitied. it’s moulded me into an incredibly strong person & i want to share the lessons i’ve learned. i experienced something no child deserves to live through
column2: but i have the privilege & power to use it in a positive way. if putting my hand up & saying me too can help a single person

column1: this is the scariest thing i’ve ever shared publicly. while i still fear the judgement & pitying looks
column2: i know i’ve nothing to feel ashamed of. i refuse to bow to that fear but i’m going to break it down for my own sanity. am i sharing too much? no
column3: my #metoo is as valid as anyone else’s. do i need your pity? no. i appreciate that it comes from a place of love but it has no use to me. can you do something to help? yes. engage in discussions about preventing sexual abuse of all kinds & help prevent the next #metoo before it happens.

column1: this is the first of countless conversations i want to have so i hope you’ll stick around to take part.

column1: 148849;instagram;2018-12-08 20:56:02;FALSE;"for those of you who don’t really know me... you’re about to. i’ve been told over and over since i was a little girl “you’re just so happy all the time! i wish i could be like that.” then to this day when people see me posing in stunning locations around the world some may be led to believe that i have it all together.

what you may not know about me is that i’ve been struggling on and off with depression and ptsd for the last two years. when you see me giggling and twirling on the santa monica pier you don’t see the number of nights i cried myself to sleep wondering if i even want to be here anymore.

column2: everyone has their demons. mine just happened to be a cocktail of sexual assault and heartbreak that sent me on a downward spiral. at a particularly low point in my life my mom told me
column3: “i hope one day you can be as happy as everyone else thinks you are.” that hit me hard.

column1: i was putting more effort into proving to those around me that i was happy with my life than going through the healing process which would lead to actual contentment. i was more interested in maintaining the facade of perfection than i was in my own mental health and well being.
so i let go of relationships that weren’t serving me
column2: a job that was killing me
column3: and a city i never really belonged in. it was an emotionally tumultuous time of my life filled with tears
column5: and my fair share of growing pains.

column1: now i am at a place where i am living out my dreams and taking on the world. i’m in love with an incredible man
column2: but more importantly i’m in love with my life and myself. i’m not yet where i want to be
column3: but i’m closer than i’ve ever been. for me

148861;instagram;2018-12-08 21:10:07;FALSE;“the last time i was here, grandpa, my sister and i were walking back over there toward the woods and witnessed a massive drug deal. it was the only time i’ve ever been really frightened by strangers. we were minding our own business, but these creeps kept staring at us. it really freaked me out, especially when one of the guys followed us back down the hill after we left. i will always remember that. he was in a sports coupe with the license plate “2wild4u”. as soon as we left the park, he slowly drove behind us all the way down the hill to one of those houses down there. it made the hair on the back of my neck stand up, and i couldn’t sleep for weeks. i was afraid that someone was going to come find me,” i said, retelling my story without much thought. “you were here with your grandpa and your sister? what were you wearing?” “what does that have to do with anything?” i asked, put off by the random question noah always managed to equate with sex. “because i think i was here that day. this was my park. i was in charge of distribution here and a few other places,” he said. -r. macceile 2018 now - dec 25th 100% of proceeds from my books column1: 148932;instagram;2018-12-09 00:06:52;FALSE;"although i may still struggle - i am very thankful for the fact that i am so much healthier than i was at this exact time one year ago. at this time
column2: i was severely underweight and preparing to go back in to residential treatment for both my eating disorder and trauma issues and i would spend the next four months working my ass off for a happier and healthier life. ever since i've been home
column3: things did not go as expected for me - but things have honestly ended up working out in my favor. i have an amazing job that i absolutely love. i am going back to school full time. i have made the life changing decision to completely cut toxic people out of my life. i have amazing sisters
column7: and an amazing boyfriend. i'm moved out on my own with wanda and we are both in such good places. my eating has improved

;já recebi várias criticas por dizer que não posso defender joão de deus , pois “ não sei como é ser abusada “ e mulheres têm que ter voz ! sim mulheres têm que ter voz , e os homens também ! pois todos têm que se manifestar em um processo , e não em um programa de televisão . post é só pra dizer que sei sim que é ser estuprada ! quando eu tinha 20 anos isso aconteceu comigo dentro meu carro por um bandido que levou pra um lugar distante , e manteve arma apontada pra minha cabeça por cerca de 8 horas . tive soe de escapar viva , e fiquei sem carro e sem chão naquele momento . minha única companhia era deus ! e ele ajuda até hoje . arrumei uma carona mesmo dia , fui até delegacia porque na época nem celular havia , e resolvi tudo sozinha porque meu pai estava cuidando da minha mãe que morreu de câncer pouco tempo depois aos 48 de idade . polícia conseguiu encontrar sujeito , ele confessou tudo e mesmo assim fiz reconhecimento dele deic e depois vi novamente dia julgamento . ele foi condenado , sentenciado e preso . e eu segui vida sem olhar pra trás , como faço até hoje . poanto pessoal e pensem que gostando ou não lugar ceo pra se dar queixa crime é na delegacia de polícia e não na rede globo com esse idiota pedro bial que chama os paicipantes bbb de “ meus heróis ” . eu também não sou heroína . quem merece esse título são os que levantam 5 da manhã para pegarem ônibus lotados e trabalham dia todo pra sustentar suas famílias ganhando um salário ridículo e sendo roubados por esses políticos safados e esses empresários sem caráter nenhum . sou só uma mulher normal e que nasceu antes tempo mimimi e desse feminismo distorcido . um feliz 2019 pra todos e pela primeira vez não vou , por razões óbvias , responder eventuais comentários desse post . 🌟 ;[('já', 'NN'), column1: 148979;instagram;2018-12-09 01:09:04;FALSE;"if you're offended by ""baby it's cold outside"" you're going to have a tough go of it in life. and so are your kids.

column2: you are completely ignoring the fact that the song is 74 years old--when women were ladies and men were gentlemen.

column1: her ""protest"" was typical of a way a lady would speak to a man instead of just downing some drinks and hopping into bed with him.
no one seems offended by those kinda lyrics when you hear them on the radio all year long.
men actually had to court women back in those days
column2: a subtle dance that for both men and women no longer exists. sad but true.
""what's in this drink?"" does not imply that she was roofied
column3: or at least it didn't in 1944. you don't need to be a historian to piece that puzzle together.

column1: she's sarcastically blaming her indecision on her drink
column3: came with the times. is that not obvious?

column1: should we stop watching the wizard of oz because when they fall asleep in the poppy fields that means dorothy is on heroin?

column2: what are you worried is going to happen?? that people will hear this song
column3: completely misinterpret the lyrics (as you obviously have) and then decide to go date rape someone?

column1: i'd like to see the #metoo movement taken seriously. uproar over a holiday song
column2: which clearly was not about abuse
my heart goes out to you
column3: but aren't we surrounded my far more obvious and offensive material on a daily basis that should be drawing the attention? is this really the right battle to fight?

column1: or maybe you're worried about your children and what they will think when they hear it? gee
column2: maybe it's the perfect teachable moment to actually sit down and have a conversation with your child about how men and women used to be. most notably
column3: not offended by everything fucking thing that crossed their path.

rudolph gets bullied in the animated version of ""rudolph the red nosed reindeer."" aaaaaaand?? wasn't that the point of the whole fucking story!!?? it's the ultimate story of redemption and turning the other cheek and doing what you gotta do in the face of adversity.

column1: “i was sexually abused by my older brother on multiple occasions
column2: from when i was too young to remember up until i was about 5 years old. i didn't understand what he was doing. he took advantage of my childhood
column3: of my innocence. i have carried this with me my entire life without being able to tell anyone. it haunts me every day and night. it emerges in anxiety attacks
column5: flashbacks and nightmares. i am afraid of my own mind
column6: afraid of remembering more of what my brain has blocked from memory. it has shaped the way i view the world. i view every woman and child as a potential victim and every boy and man as a potential predator. it is exhausting. i can tell no one. i have no way of explaining why i am the way i am to anyone: why i get triggered
column7: why i have to leave class to cry in the bathroom for an hour
column8: why i am afraid to leave the safety of my own locked room
column9: why i can't let my guard down around men and boys
column10: why i have to sleep all day to make up for the nights of sleep i lost because the memories return in the darkness. i carry this burden alone. i feel responsible for holding my family together
column12: even my brother's life. it would tear him apart if he knew i remembered. even worse
column13: i feel responsible for the safety of my brother's future children. i know what he is capable of
column15: and how he acted out on them at a young age - cementing those tendencies into realities that will make it easier for him to do it again to any other child in his life. i don't know what to do.” -anonymous

column1:
;pernyataan sikap : dewan pimpi pusat aksi perempuan indonesia ( api ) kaini indonesia darurat kekerasan seksual , sahkan ruu p-ks ! indonesia merdeka , yang diikhtiarkan oleh para pendiri bangsa , akan menjadi salah satu tempat di muka bumi ini yang memberi tempat pada kesetaraan gender . tidak ada diskriminasi , eksploitasi , maupun kekerasan , apalagi berbasis gender . sayang sekali , hingga 73 tahun merdeka , indonesia merdeka belum menjadi tempat yang nyaman dan aman bagi perempuan . lihat saja kasus baiq nuril , agni di jogjakaa , frisca di ntt , pemerkosaan anak pengungsi gempa sulteng di makassar , dan masih banyak lagi . hasil pendataan survei pengalaman hidup perempuan nasional ( sphpn ) bps tahun 2016 menunjukkan , 1 dari 3 perempuan usia 15-64 tahun pernah mengalami kekerasan fisik atau seksual oleh pasangan maupun non-pasangan . sementara data komnas perempuan menunjukkan , setiap harinya ada 35 perempuan indonesia yang mengalami kekerasan seksual . ainya , dalam tiap dua jam , ada tiga perempuan yang mengalami kekerasan seksual . boleh dikatakan , indonesia sedang mengalami “ darurat kekerasan seksual ” . ironisnya , sementara indonesia mengalami darurat kekerasan seksual , negara ini belum berhasil menghadirkan regulasi yang benar-benar melindungi perempuan . aturan yang ada sekarang , yakni kuhp , masih mengidap logika jongkok warisan patriarki dalam memahami kekerasan seksual . mulai dari defenisi , cakupan , hingga ancaman hukuman . di sisi lain , aparat penegak hukum yang harusnya menjadi ujung tombak penegakan hak korban kekerasan seksual , juga banyak mengidap penyakit patriarkal . belum lagi , banyak pelaku kekerasan seksual , terutama yang punya relasi kuasa , menikmati impunitas . ditambah lagi , akibat konstruksi sosial yang patriarkis , relasi kuasa , dan budaya pembisuan , banyak kasus kekerasan seksual yang mendapat pembiaran , tidak terlaporkan , dan tidak teradvokasi . selengkapnya di apikaini.org/ *nb : dalam bberpaa foto , ribuan kami yang tergabung dalam gerakan masyarakat utk pengesahan ruu p-ks , turun kejalan mendesak agar ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual segra disahkan ! 6haktp erakbersama
